								<event>
									<text>"Lad, have you ever heard of the Greek religion," Alastair asks. "I learned about it in a book about humans. There's a myth about a three-headed dog named Cerberus who protects the gates to hell. The only thing more fearsome than this dog would be my daughter Lucille asking me for a dog." Alastair hammers on the weapon a few times and looks up. "I told her that this is no ship for a dog, but she insisted that she wanted three. I finally managed to talk her out of it, but I'm not quite sure if she forgives me for that one. If you ever come across her, ask her for me would ya?"</text>  <!--Fourth locked in screen, shows nothing but the text TOP text part here-->
