<textList name="TEXT_CREW_TALK_PLATED" ignoreUnique="true">
	<text>Your Plated Rockman is busy building a miniature model of your ship. They show it to you, it is very well made and accurate.</text>
	<text>Your Plated Rockman shows you the conductor figurine they are painting for their miniature train set. It is painted with utmost care.</text>
	<text>Your Plated Rockman tells you that they wish they could design a 1:1000 scale model train, but their hands are too big.</text>
	<text>Your Plated Rockman tells you that they really enjoy hearing Alastair laugh.</text>
	<text>Your Plated Rockman is writing a letter, presumably to their family or friends. It would be best not to bother them.</text>
	<text>Your Plated Rockman tells you a story about how one time Alastair dropped his wedding ring into the forge. He slammed his arm into the forge so fast to get it out he nearly broke the forge.</text>
	<text>Your Plated Rockman tells you about an object they read about in a book called a "kite". They ask if you would like to go fly one sometime on a nearby planet.</text>
	<text>You walk in to observe your Plated Rockman using a nearby wall to scratch their back. You decide to leave them to their business.</text>
	<text>Your spot your Plated Rockman at the cafeteria, they are eating enough to kill a bear. You sit next to them and they clap you on the back with their arm, a hearty grin on their face.  You dont have the heart to tell them they almost broke your back. </text>
	<text>Your Plate Rockman bashfully approaches you and asks if the hat they are wearing looks good with their duds. You don't have the heart to tell them a top hat doesn't match electroplating.</text>
	<text>You ask your Plated Rockman what they thinks about the Mantis. They think on it for a moment, then responds "They make cool bombs. I love taking them apart." You're pretty sure thats what you meant.</text>
	<text>Some of your crew complain about the heat being too high. You catch the culprit, your Plated Rockman. They claim it is "too cold on the ship." The crew is sweating so much that they could fill a swimming pool, you scold them to not do this anymore.</text>
	<text>You asked your Plated Rockman how Alastair comes across some of his weapon recipes. The Plated coughs loudly and then asks you about the weather. Looks like that subject is off-limits.</text>
	<text>You ask your Plated Rockman if they ever wants to be the captain of their own ship. They explain that they love gathering new skills, so why not? </text>
	<text>Your Plated Rockman remarks that they hope there is a good forge in the afterlife, so they can continue to hone their craft just like Alastair. </text>
	<text>You hear a knock at your door. You open it to find your Plated Rockman standing there. "Why didn't humans just build railroads in space?" they ask suddenly. You close the door on him.</text>
	<text>Your Plated Rockman asks where the furnace and bellows are in your ship. You inform them you don't have one, and they throw their arms in the air and storm off in a huff.</text>
	<text>You ask your Plated Rockman about their family. You are treated to a lovely story about their grandmother's cooking. You ponder over what it actually tastes like.</text>
	<text>Your Plated Rockman dislikes that fact that your ship has no music at all, and fashions some make-shift drums out of some scrap metal. The sound they make is awful and you confiscate them.</text>
	<text>Your Plated Rockman thinks you shouldn't trust Engis because of their disgusting food. They explain: "If your cuisine is nasty, you're probably evil." You mentally note to never cook for this individual.</text>
	<text>Your plated Rockman is playing with their train track that they bought aboard, but they probably will waste your time if you ask them about it</text>
</textList>

